chunk_content: How to collect: The numerator can be generated by counting the number of people who are newly enrolled on PrEP in the reporting period, in accordance with national guidelines (or WHO/UNAIDS standards). NEW is a state defined by an individual’s starting PrEP for the first time (outside of any clinical trial participation). It is expected that the characteristics of new users are recorded at the time they newly initiate into a program. Individuals are “new” on PrEP only if they are naive to antiretroviral therapy for prevention of HIV infection in a program implementation setting and have not received oral or topical PrEP previously in any program at any other time. An individual should NOT be counted as NEW if they have previously taken any type of PrEP, even if they are changing to a new PrEP type (e.g., from oral to injectable PrEP).
